Package: gspy
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: forensic goroutine-to-syscall inspector for Go processes
 gspy attaches to a running Go process by PID using eBPF uprobes and
 kernel tracepoints, mapping goroutine IDs to active kernel syscalls
 and user-space stack frames in real time.
 .
 No ptrace, no instrumentation, no process restart, and no modification
 of the target binary's memory or file hash is required. Goroutine IDs
 are extracted via thread-local storage using process_vm_readv(2).
 .
 Features include forensic readonly mode with SHA-256 binary attestation,
 JSON output for pipeline integration, and a live terminal UI.
 .
 Requires Linux kernel 5.8 or later with BPF syscall support enabled
 (CONFIG_BPF_SYSCALL=y) and either CAP_BPF + CAP_PERFMON or
 CAP_SYS_ADMIN.
